sub_title: Founder of Sea Going Green | Forbes 30 under 30 | UNLEASH Talent | TNW 500
summary:
üöÄCEO & Founder of Sea Going Green, a sustainable tourism advisory specialised in carbon footprint measuring and managing for the marine tourism industry. Our mission is to alleviate the negative impacts of the tourism industry on the (marine) environment. Part of ACE - #1 Incubator in the NL (Emerce100) , Rockstart Femteq by INCO, JPMorgan Chase & Co, Adyen Accelerator Program.

üå± Our green transition strategies make our clients future proof and equipped to protect the destination their tourism products rely on, ensuring they will be profitable for years to come.

üî• My strengths lie in business development, partnerships and customer relations & management.

üåä Being a marine biologist, and coming from academia becoming an entrepreneur has been one of the largest learning curves of my life- but also one of the most enjoyable! Previously having worked in the tourism sector, and travelling for most of my life I was always looking how to combine my career and passions together ‚Äì the oceans & travelling while making a positive impact. My passion lies in supporting others on their entrepreneurial journey and sharing my story. 

üèÜ Forbes 30 Under 30 Europe 2019 as a top social entrepreneur.
üèÜ Semi-finalist TedxAmsterdam Women‚Äôs Startup Awards 2018, Semi-finalist ATECH Aruba Tech Awards 2018
üèÜ TNW 500 2018 Top Digital Entrepreneurs, VIVA 400 2018 ‚Äì Top Female Entrepreneurs 

Invited speaker to tech and startup events covering topics on sustainability, sustainable tourism, marine pollution, plastic pollution, marine tourism, tech, females, entrepreneurship. Such as:
‚ö°DAVOS- World Biodiversity Forum 2022
‚ö°Marine Debris Conference Korea (7IMDC) 2022
‚ö°Booking Manager Summit Croatia
‚ö°US State department Innovation Station 2021
‚ö°Toronto Global Forum with IEFA 2021
‚ö°ANVR Sustainability Day (NL) 2019
‚ö°Road to GES Cura√ßao 2019
‚ö°Build Back Better Week Saint Martin 2018

Board member of the International Alumni Network for the University of Amsterdam, UNLEASH Talent Greenland 2022.

Featured by Forbes, World Economic Forum, Entrepreneur, NWO ‚Äì Netherlands Institute for Scientific Research.

Reach out at : ally@seagoinggreen.org
